Republic of Ireland manager Stephen Kenny’s managerial contract has been extended until 2024, the Football Association of Ireland (FAI) said on Wednesday. Kenny will continue to lead the national soccer team through the 2024 Uefa European Championship campaign. New contracts have also been agreed for assistant manager Keith Andrews and coaching staff members Dean Kiely, Stephen Rice and Damien Doyle. “The attitude of the players has been exceptional, we have seen the team grow and develop and I, together with Keith Andrews and all of the staff, look forward to seeing the team fulfil its potential,” Kenny said. “ With the recent return of supporters to stadiums, I want to acknowledge the importance of the passionate Irish fans both home and away.” More to follow ...